OL,3,CUrgent calls to upgrade one of the
OL,4,Cworld's smallest working jails
OL,6,FThere are urgent calls to upgrade one
OL,7,Fof the world's smallest working jails.
OL,9,FThe Channel Island of Sark, which is
OL,10,Fhome to around 500 people, is not
OL,11,Fknown for high crime rates.
OL,13,FHowever, the crumbling granite prison,
OL,14,Fbuilt in 1856, is deemed no longer fit
OL,15,Ffor purpose and does not meet modern
OL,16,Fpolicing standards, according to the
OL,17,Fisland's Constables.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/6
